----------------------------------------------
swerc_inflate_cut.c

  creates permutominoes with n-vertices defined in CCW order
  coordinates x and y from 0 to n/2-1

  ** w.r.t. CANONICAL cartesian system if STANDARD_Y_AXIS active 

  ** w.r.t  non canonical system (y-axis reversed) if SYM_STANDARD_Y_AXIS active 


  Input data:
    K n
    where K is the number of instances to be created

  Ouput data:
    K lines, each one defines a permutomino with n vertices
    Each permutomino is given by  n  v_1 ... v_n  in CCW order


   -----------------
   REMARK:
   -------------------
       if SYM_STANDARD_Y_AXIS is active but we take it as if 
       the coordinates were in the canonical cartesian system, 
       the sequence of vertices of the polygon will be in CW order,
       wrt the canonical system.

--------------------------------------------------

draw_orthopol.c

   creates image to be processed by LaTeX 
   assumes coordinates given wrt canonical referential system
    ((1,0),(0,1)), but can be used to produce a (flipped) image
   even with coordinates given in wrt ((1,0),(-1,0))

   input data:
     n  v_1  v_2  ... v_n
     given in CW order  

   REMARK: we can use swerc_inflate_cut.c with SYM_STANDARD_Y_AXIS
   to create the polygon

----------------------------------------------------
expconvert.c

 receives a permutomino in CW  and shifts the edges by inserting
 new gridlines.

    This program allows us to create rectilinear polygons that
    are not permutominoes 

____________________________________________________________________________
____________________________________________________________________________

gridnew.c   

  computes H/V partition

  applies sweeping to compute the rectilinear partition of an orthogonal
  polygon without collinear edges

  ASSUMES:  sequence of vertices in CCW order and 
            REF AXES  ((1,0), (0,-1))   NOT CANONICAL
                 ------>
                 |
                 |
		 V

  


----------------------------------------------------

hpartition.c -- computes H-partition

   assumes sequence of vertices in CCW order and 
            REF AXES  ((1,0), (0,-1))   NOT CANONICAL
                 ------>
                 |
                 |
		 V


---------------------------------------------------------

draw_orthopol.c   
 
Sequence of vertices of the polygon 

(picture as if coordinates were given in canonical ref)

-----------------------------------

draw_partition.c

Sequence of vertices of the polygon 
half-edges of the partition   X Y  Xf Yf

(picture as if coordinates were given in canonical ref)


_____________________________________________________________________

The programs in the archive were written to run independently:

$ gcc -o swerc_inflate_cut swerc_inflate_cut.c
$ gcc -o expconvert expconvert.c


$ gcc -o distr_Inflate_sym distr_Inflate.c

$ gcc -o gridnew gridnew.c
$ gcc -o hpartition hpartition.c

$ gcc -o draw_orthopol draw_orthopol.c 
$ gcc -o draw_partition draw_partition.c


-----------------

Example of usage:

$ swerc_inflate_cut > exemplo
1 12

(to create 1 permutomino with n=12)

$ draw_orthopol < exemplo > exemplo.tex
  
$ pdflatex exemplo.tex

$ evince exemplo.pdf &
( or acroread exemplo.pdf & )

$ expconvert  < exemplo > exemplo_transf

$ draw_orthopol < exemplo_transf > exemplo_transf.tex

$ pdflatex exemplo_transf.tex  & 

$ gridnew  < exemplo_transf > exemplo_transf_grid

$ hpartition  < exemplo_transf > exemplo_transf_hp

$ draw_partition < exemplo_transf_grid > exemplo_transf_grid.tex

$ draw_partition < exemplo_transf_hp > exemplo_transf_hp.tex

